# case.ttl -- the concrete Meridian Holdings Group / Corvantis Systems
# acquisition scenario, the instance-data companion to
# packs/ma-case-study-pack/ontology.ttl + shapes.ttl (built the same session,
# see this pack's pack.toml for the vocabulary-fit research those two files
# implement). Per docs/releases/v26.7.14/THESIS.md Section 33.12: unlike the
# bribery case's single allegation spine
# (crates/multifractal-workflow/fixtures/bribery-case/case.ttl), an
# acquisition contains SEVERAL INDEPENDENT external service processes; this
# file asserts real instance data across all 6 named in that section, not
# just the 4-of-6 floor the task set:
#
#   1. buyer diligence            -> 3 ma:DueDiligenceItem individuals
#   2. seller disclosure           -> 1 ma:DisclosureScheduleItem qualifying
#                                      the no-material-litigation Warranty
#   3. financing                   -> 1 ma:FinancingCommitment + its
#                                      ma:FinancingOutCondition
#   4. regulatory review           -> the raw schema:amount fact this pack's
#                                      fixtures/hook.ttl pattern-matches to
#                                      DERIVE the HSR filing obligation (see
#                                      that file -- the obligation link is
#                                      NOT asserted here, only observed raw
#                                      facts are; see OBSERVATION-ONLY FENCE
#                                      below)
#   5. board authority             -> 1 ma:BoardResolution authorizing the
#                                      MergerAcquisition
#   6. shareholder action          -> 1 ma:ShareholderVote + 3 ma:Ballot
#
# SCOPE, HONESTLY STATED: this file is NOT run through F02 observation
# admission (multifractal_workflow::f02_observation_admission) the way
# bribery-case/case.ttl is -- that mechanism was purpose-built for a single
# admitted-case-per-allegation shape and standing up an equivalent
# AdmissionPolicy for a 6-process M&A case is real, non-trivial design work
# this task's own scope carve-out excludes ("this session's job is real
# vocabulary+ontology+case+hook progress, not the full crown chain"). This
# file is proven instead via the same `TripleStore::load_hook_pack` +
# `.materialize()` mechanism `packs/soc2-audit-pack`'s own
# `soc2_hook_actuation.rs` and bribery-case's `hook.ttl` already exercise in
# production-shaped form -- see
# `crates/praxis-graphlaw/tests/ma_case_hook_actuation.rs`, which loads this
# exact file (via `include_str!`) together with `hook.ttl` and shows the
# regulatory-filing-obligation hook fires over it.
#
# INSTANCE-IRI STYLE: mirrors bribery-case/case.ttl exactly -- every instance
# below is a full angle-bracket IRI, not a prefixed name, because Turtle's
# PN_LOCAL grammar does not allow an unescaped `/` inside a prefixed local
# name (the natural `<base>/kind/local-name` path shape this fixture and
# bribery-case's own case.ttl both use). Only VOCABULARY terms (ma:, FIBO,
# OMG Commons, PROV-O, schema.org, Dublin Core) are prefixed.
#
# FICTIONAL-ENTITY CONVENTION (same discipline
# crates/multifractal-workflow/fixtures/bribery-case/case.ttl states in its
# own header for "Solvane Global"/"Nilsson Consulting AB"): every company,
# person, and LEI code below is invented for this fixture. "Meridian
# Holdings Group, Inc.", "Corvantis Systems, Inc.", "FirstCap Partners",
# "Alpha Capital Partners", "Beta Pension Trust", and "Gamma Family Office"
# do not refer to any real acquirer, target, lender, or shareholder; the LEI
# codes below are synthetic 20-character strings in the right SHAPE (per
# ISO 17442) but are not registered GLEIF identifiers and must never be
# treated as real ones. The Hart-Scott-Rodino Act citation (15 U.S.C. §18a)
# and its 30-day standard waiting period are real, publicly documented facts
# about U.S. antitrust law reused for narrative realism; the specific
# ma:filingThresholdAmount value ($100,000,000) is this fixture's own
# ILLUSTRATIVE round figure, not asserted as the exact, annually-adjusted
# current HSR Act size-of-transaction threshold (a real number this pack
# does not track and this fixture does not depend on being current).
#
# PUBLIC-ONTOLOGY-FIRST: every class/property below is either reused
# directly from FIBO/OMG-Commons/ODRL/PROV-O/schema.org/Dublin Core (see
# ontology.ttl's header for the full grounding citations) or one of this
# pack's own disclosed ma: bridge terms -- no new vocabulary is minted in
# this file. schema:amount + schema:MonetaryAmount (schema:value +
# schema:currency) model the deal's aggregate consideration, the same
# public-term choice bribery-case/case.ttl makes for its transaction amount
# (schema:amount's own domainIncludes is permissive; schema.org properties
# are usable on any type by design). dcterms:identifier carries the LEI
# code's literal value on each fibo-be-le-lei:LegalEntityIdentifier
# individual: cmns-id: is not vendored in this repo (ontology.ttl's header
# already discloses this), so the literal-carrying property on that OMG
# Commons class could not be independently re-verified this session;
# dcterms:identifier is reused instead (the same property bribery-case's
# case.ttl already uses for its own human-facing case number), not a new
# minted property.
#
# OBSERVATION-ONLY FENCE (mirrors bribery-case/case.ttl's own fence): this
# file records what is KNOWN about the deal as of the case's signing +
# board/shareholder actions -- it never asserts a hook-derived fact directly
# (no ma:hasRegulatoryFilingObligation triple appears below; that link is
# exactly what fixtures/hook.ttl's Knowledge Hook exists to derive). The
# deal's ma:DealStatus is ma:PendingRegulatoryApproval, consistent with a
# signed-but-not-yet-closed transaction still inside its HSR waiting period.

@prefix rdf:              <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> .
@prefix xsd:               <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .
@prefix prov:              <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#> .
@prefix dcterms:           <http://purl.org/dc/terms/> .
@prefix schema:            <https://schema.org/> .
@prefix odrl:              <http://www.w3.org/ns/odrl/2/> .
@prefix cmns-bauth:        <https://www.omg.org/spec/Commons/BusinessAuthorizations/> .
@prefix cmns-cls:          <https://www.omg.org/spec/Commons/Classifiers/> .
@prefix cmns-id:           <https://www.omg.org/spec/Commons/Identifiers/> .
@prefix fibo-be-le-lei:    <https://spec.edmcouncil.org/fibo/ontology/BE/LegalEntities/LEIEntities/> .
@prefix fibo-be-oac-exec:  <https://spec.edmcouncil.org/fibo/ontology/BE/OwnershipAndControl/Executives/> .
@prefix fibo-be-oac-cctl:  <https://spec.edmcouncil.org/fibo/ontology/BE/OwnershipAndControl/CorporateControl/> .
@prefix fibo-fnd-agr-ctr:  <https://spec.edmcouncil.org/fibo/ontology/FND/Agreements/Contracts/> .
@prefix fibo-cae-ce-act:   <https://spec.edmcouncil.org/fibo/ontology/CAE/CorporateEvents/CorporateActions/> .
@prefix ma:                <http://seanchatmangpt.github.io/packs/ma-case-study#> .

# ── Vocabulary restatement, disclosed: `ggen graph validate --files` (the
#    version available this session) validates each --files entry AGAINST
#    THE SHAPES INDEPENDENTLY, not as a union with the other --files
#    entries -- confirmed empirically this session (a merged
#    ontology.ttl+case.ttl temp file validates shapes_conform: true; the
#    same two files passed side-by-side via --files do not, because
#    ma:MergerAcquisitionShape's `sh:class ma:DealStatus` check on the
#    cmns-cls:isClassifiedBy value needs that value's `a ma:DealStatus`
#    triple present IN THE SAME VALIDATED FILE, and ontology.ttl (where
#    ma:PendingRegulatoryApproval's type lives) is a separate file). The one
#    line below restates that single, already-true TBox fact so this file
#    passes real SHACL evaluation standalone -- exactly the same choice
#    bribery-case/case.ttl makes by declaring its OWN sc:CaseStatusScheme
#    individuals inline rather than in a separate file, not a new mint.

ma:PendingRegulatoryApproval a ma:DealStatus .

# ── Concept 1: LEI-registered legal entities (acquirer + target) ──────────

<https://deals.meridian-holdings.example.org/identifier/lei-meridian-holdings-group>
    a fibo-be-le-lei:LegalEntityIdentifier ;
    dcterms:identifier "5493001234MERIDIANHG" .

<https://deals.meridian-holdings.example.org/entity/acquirer-meridian-holdings-group>
    a fibo-be-le-lei:LEIRegisteredEntity ;
    fibo-be-le-lei:hasLegalFormAbbreviation "INC" ;
    cmns-id:isIdentifiedBy <https://deals.meridian-holdings.example.org/identifier/lei-meridian-holdings-group> ;
    dcterms:description "Acquirer: Meridian Holdings Group, Inc. (Delaware), a fictional diversified industrial holding company." .

<https://deals.meridian-holdings.example.org/identifier/lei-corvantis-systems>
    a fibo-be-le-lei:LegalEntityIdentifier ;
    dcterms:identifier "5493005678CORVANTISX" .

<https://deals.meridian-holdings.example.org/entity/target-corvantis-systems>
    a fibo-be-le-lei:LEIRegisteredEntity ;
    fibo-be-le-lei:hasLegalFormAbbreviation "INC" ;
    cmns-id:isIdentifiedBy <https://deals.meridian-holdings.example.org/identifier/lei-corvantis-systems> ;
    dcterms:description "Target: Corvantis Systems, Inc. (California), a fictional industrial-automation software company." .

# ── Concept 2: the ownership interest to be acquired ───────────────────────

<https://deals.meridian-holdings.example.org/relationship/MHC-2026-0091-ownership>
    a fibo-be-le-lei:RelationshipRecord ;
    fibo-be-le-lei:hasOwnershipPercentage "100.00"^^xsd:decimal ;
    dcterms:description "Full (100%) ownership interest in Corvantis Systems, Inc. to be acquired by Meridian Holdings Group, Inc. upon closing." .

# ── The deal itself (reused fibo-cae-ce-act:MergerAcquisition + ma:DealStatus) ──

<https://deals.meridian-holdings.example.org/deal/MHC-2026-0091>
    a fibo-cae-ce-act:MergerAcquisition ;
    cmns-cls:isClassifiedBy ma:PendingRegulatoryApproval ;
    schema:amount [
        a schema:MonetaryAmount ;
        schema:value 725000000 ;
        schema:currency "USD"
    ] ;
    dcterms:description "Meridian Holdings Group, Inc. definitive agreement to acquire 100% of Corvantis Systems, Inc. for aggregate consideration of USD 725,000,000, signed 2026-03-28." .

# ── Process 2 (setup): the Representation and Warranty this deal's
#    disclosure schedule qualifies -- concept 4 ─────────────────────────────

<https://deals.meridian-holdings.example.org/clause/rep-target-financial-statements>
    a fibo-fnd-agr-ctr:Representation ;
    dcterms:description "Corvantis Systems, Inc. represents that its audited FY2025 financial statements fairly present its financial condition in all material respects." .

<https://deals.meridian-holdings.example.org/clause/warranty-target-no-material-litigation>
    a fibo-fnd-agr-ctr:Warranty ;
    dcterms:description "Corvantis Systems, Inc. warrants that there is no pending or threatened litigation that would have a material adverse effect on the business, except as set forth on the disclosure schedule." .

# ── Process 2: seller disclosure -- the one carve-out into the warranty
#    above (concept 4, private half) ────────────────────────────────────────

<https://deals.meridian-holdings.example.org/disclosure/schedule-3-14-b-pending-litigation>
    a ma:DisclosureScheduleItem ;
    ma:qualifiesClause <https://deals.meridian-holdings.example.org/clause/warranty-target-no-material-litigation> ;
    ma:scheduleItemNumber "Schedule 3.14(b)" .

# ── Process 1: buyer diligence -- 3 checklist items in 3 different
#    dispositions (concept 3) ───────────────────────────────────────────────

<https://deals.meridian-holdings.example.org/ddi/ip-assignment-review>
    a ma:DueDiligenceItem ;
    odrl:target <https://deals.meridian-holdings.example.org/entity/target-corvantis-systems> ;
    ma:dueDiligenceDisposition ma:Satisfied .

<https://deals.meridian-holdings.example.org/ddi/customer-contract-consent-assignments>
    a ma:DueDiligenceItem ;
    odrl:target <https://deals.meridian-holdings.example.org/entity/target-corvantis-systems> ;
    ma:dueDiligenceDisposition ma:Open .

<https://deals.meridian-holdings.example.org/ddi/environmental-phase-2-survey>
    a ma:DueDiligenceItem ;
    odrl:target <https://deals.meridian-holdings.example.org/entity/target-corvantis-systems> ;
    ma:dueDiligenceDisposition ma:Waived .

# ── Process 3: financing -- a debt-commitment letter subject to a
#    financing-out condition (concept 9) ────────────────────────────────────

<https://deals.meridian-holdings.example.org/financing/condition-no-material-adverse-change>
    a ma:FinancingOutCondition ;
    dcterms:description "The debt commitment is contingent on no Material Adverse Change occurring in Corvantis Systems, Inc.'s business between signing and closing." .

<https://deals.meridian-holdings.example.org/financing/debt-commitment-firstcap-partners>
    a ma:FinancingCommitment ;
    dcterms:description "FirstCap Partners debt-commitment letter for USD 400,000,000 of acquisition financing." ;
    ma:subjectToCondition <https://deals.meridian-holdings.example.org/financing/condition-no-material-adverse-change> .

# ── Process 5: board authority -- Meridian's board resolution authorizing
#    the transaction (concept 6) ────────────────────────────────────────────

<https://deals.meridian-holdings.example.org/agent/board-of-directors-meridian>
    a fibo-be-oac-exec:BoardOfDirectors .

<https://deals.meridian-holdings.example.org/agent/ceo-meridian-authorized-signatory>
    a cmns-bauth:AuthorizedParty ;
    dcterms:description "Chief Executive Officer of Meridian Holdings Group, Inc., authorized by board resolution to execute the definitive agreement." .

<https://deals.meridian-holdings.example.org/authorization/board-resolution-meridian-2026-03-28>
    a ma:BoardResolution ;
    cmns-bauth:hasAuthorizingParty <https://deals.meridian-holdings.example.org/agent/board-of-directors-meridian> ;
    cmns-bauth:hasAuthorizedParty <https://deals.meridian-holdings.example.org/agent/ceo-meridian-authorized-signatory> ;
    ma:authorizesTransaction <https://deals.meridian-holdings.example.org/deal/MHC-2026-0091> ;
    prov:generatedAtTime "2026-03-28T16:00:00Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

# ── Process 6: shareholder action -- Corvantis's shareholder vote approving
#    the transaction (concept 7) ────────────────────────────────────────────

<https://deals.meridian-holdings.example.org/agent/shareholder-alpha-capital-partners>
    a fibo-be-oac-cctl:VotingShareholder ;
    dcterms:description "Alpha Capital Partners, a fictional institutional shareholder of Corvantis Systems, Inc." .

<https://deals.meridian-holdings.example.org/agent/shareholder-beta-pension-trust>
    a fibo-be-oac-cctl:VotingShareholder ;
    dcterms:description "Beta Pension Trust, a fictional institutional shareholder of Corvantis Systems, Inc." .

<https://deals.meridian-holdings.example.org/agent/shareholder-gamma-family-office>
    a fibo-be-oac-cctl:VotingShareholder ;
    dcterms:description "Gamma Family Office, a fictional institutional shareholder of Corvantis Systems, Inc." .

<https://deals.meridian-holdings.example.org/vote/target-shareholder-vote-2026-05-15>
    a ma:ShareholderVote ;
    ma:quorumPercentage "82.50"^^xsd:decimal ;
    ma:voteOutcome ma:Passed .

<https://deals.meridian-holdings.example.org/ballot/ballot-001-alpha>
    a ma:Ballot ;
    dcterms:isPartOf <https://deals.meridian-holdings.example.org/vote/target-shareholder-vote-2026-05-15> ;
    prov:wasAttributedTo <https://deals.meridian-holdings.example.org/agent/shareholder-alpha-capital-partners> ;
    ma:ballotDirection ma:For .

<https://deals.meridian-holdings.example.org/ballot/ballot-002-beta>
    a ma:Ballot ;
    dcterms:isPartOf <https://deals.meridian-holdings.example.org/vote/target-shareholder-vote-2026-05-15> ;
    prov:wasAttributedTo <https://deals.meridian-holdings.example.org/agent/shareholder-beta-pension-trust> ;
    ma:ballotDirection ma:For .

<https://deals.meridian-holdings.example.org/ballot/ballot-003-gamma>
    a ma:Ballot ;
    dcterms:isPartOf <https://deals.meridian-holdings.example.org/vote/target-shareholder-vote-2026-05-15> ;
    prov:wasAttributedTo <https://deals.meridian-holdings.example.org/agent/shareholder-gamma-family-office> ;
    ma:ballotDirection ma:Against .
